stork.scheduler

Class Job

  • java.lang.Object
    • stork.scheduler.Job

  • public class Job
extends Object
    A job that should be scheduled to run. Currently this only means transfer jobs. In the future we will likely have different types of jobs, such as deletion jobs.

      • restart

        public Job restart()
        Completely restarts the job. This will reset any state associated with the job and start it again as if it is the first time it has been seen by the system. This should only ever be called as a result of a user request.
